<DOCNO> AP890623-0011 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-06-23-89 0047EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a PM-Overweight-Stats     06-23 0304</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Overweight-Stats,0338</SECOND>
<HEAD>With PM-Overweight</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are state-by-state results from the U.S.
Centers for Disease Control survey of overweight adults in 32
participating states and the District of Columbia. Listed in order,
from highest to lowest, are the percentages of surveyed people in
each state who indicated they are overweight, for all respondents,
for men and for women.
   
   Indiana, 25.7 percent, men 26.8, women 24.6.
   Wisconsin, 25.7 percent, men 26.9, women 24.6.
   West Virginia, 25.1 percent, men 26.4, women 23.9.
   Ohio, 25.0 percent, men 26.8, women 23.3.
   North Dakota, 23.2 percent, men 23.5, women 22.9.
