<FIRST>r a PM-LynchTrial     06-23 0446</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Lynch Trial,0460</SECOND>
<HEAD>Woman Found Guilty Of Killing Couple, Snatching Baby</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By THERESA HUMPHREY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>DOVER, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman was convicted of killing a couple to
steal their 9-day-old son, and the victims' family will be satisfied
whether she is sentenced to death or life in prison without parole,
a family spokesman said.
   The Kent County Superior Court jury that convicted Joyce Lynch on
Thursday was to begin deciding between those two possible sentences
today.
   Mrs. Lynch was convicted of killing Joseph and Beverly Gibson,
snatching their infant son Matthew and trying to pass him off as her
own.
   ``We're satisfied that at this point, for the rest of her life,
she won't hurt anybody else. She won't murder anybody else,'' said
the Rev. Kenneth Valentine, a spokesman for the Gibson family.
   Valentine said family members would not comment on whether they
had a preference for punishment.
   The state is seeking the death penalty. Delaware has seven men on
death row. The last woman executed was May H. Carey, who was hanged
June 7, 1935.
   Mrs. Lynch, 36, and her 27-year-old husband, Richard, stalked the
Gibson couple for at least a week before gunning them down at their
mobile home on Christmas Eve 1987, the prosecution said in closing
arguments after 16 days of testimony.
   The Lynches have accused each other in the slayings, and are
being tried separately. Lynch faces trial in September.
   They were each charged with two counts of murder, two counts of
felony murder, one count of conspiracy, and one count of possession
of a deadly weapon during the commission of a felony, burglary and
unlawful imprisonment.
   When the Lynches were arrested on Jan. 7, 1988, they had Matthew,
whom they claimed was Richard Lynch III. Police found them by
tracing telephone calls from their Houston home to the Gibson's.
   Mrs. Lynch claimed her husband controlled her by injecting her
with overdoses of a painkiller she needed for a back ailment. She
said she thought the killings were a dream until her husband told
her they had actually killed the couple.
   The prosecution, however, contended Mrs. Lynch was the mastermind
and duped her husband into thinking she was pregnant. The
prosecution said she knew she had a hysterectomy in 1978 and could
not have children. She has two children from a previous marriage.
   Gibson, 32, was found in a pool of blood by his then-5-year-old
daughter, Rebecca, and 1-year-old son, John Gregory.
   Mrs. Gibson, 27, was found slumped over the steering wheel of her
car, clutching the cloth diaper she used when burping Matthew.
   Matthew and his brother and sister have been raised by their
paternal grandparents.
</TEXT>
