   A jury was chosen for the trial of two
former PTL aides of Jim Bakker after a judge asked potential
panelists if they contributed to a church or recognized luxury
brands like Cartier and Mercedes-Benz.
   Twelve jurors and four alternates were selected Thursday to hear
the trial of David Taggart, 32, and his 35-year-old brother and
housemate, James.
   They are accused of not paying $494,000 in income taxes from 1983
to 1987 and of using more than $1.1 million of PTL money to pay
personal bills, including $55,000 for purchases from the Cartier
jewelry store in New York.
