<HEAD>Two Ships Collide Off Spain, One Dead, Two Hurt, Five Misssing</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Subs 2 grafs for last pvs, ``The official...'' to ADD Melouiya's
cargo and destination. No pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VIGO, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two cargo ships collided in heavy fog off
northwestern Spain today and one sank, killing one sailor and
injuring two, a navy official said. Rescue workers were searching
for five missing crew members.
   The Cypriot-registered Lady Rhoda had eight sailors aboard when
it sank after colliding at 3 a.m. with the Moroccan vessel Melouiya
12.5 miles off the port of Cabo Silleiro, a Spanish navy official
said.
   Two Lady Rhoda sailors were slightly injured, one died and the
other five were missing, said the official, who spoke on condition
of anonymity.
   He said there were no injuries among the eight crewmen of the
Melouiya. Authorities towed the ship to Vigo, where its damaged prow
will be rebuilt.
   Two Spanish air force helicopters, two Spanish navy patrol boats,
a Portuguese navy vessel and several Red Cross launches were
searching in foggy conditions for the missing sailors, he said.
   The Lady Rhoda, a 500-ton, 165-foot vessel, was hauling wood from
Suez to the British port of Rochester, the official said. Portuguese
news reports said it left the northern Portuguese port of Leixoes on
Thursday night.
   The official said the Melouiya was roughly the same size as the
Lady Rhoda.
   The Melouiya reportedly was headed for Morocco with a cargo of
iron and chemicals it picked up in the Spanish port of Bilbao.
</TEXT>
