<HEAD>Hotel Fire Kills 10, Injures 10</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fire swept through a hotel in eastern
Taiwan on Thursday, killing 10 people and injuring 10 others, police
said.
   About a dozen other people were rescued from the Huachi Hotel
after the fire engulfed the top three floors of the eight-story
building, according to police in Hualien, 120 miles southeast of
Taipei.
   Among the dead were three men and two women, aged between 17 and
18, who had come from Hong Kong to tour the scenic Taroko Gorge near
Hualien, police said.
   Wu Ro-mei, 20, of Hong Kong, jumped from the top floor of the
hotel and suffered serious fractures, a nurse at Hualien Hospital
said.
   Authorities were investigating on the cause of the fire.
