<SECOND>AM-BRF--Japan-US,0115</SECOND>
<HEAD>U.S. Navy to Move Task Force-70 to Japan From Philippines</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The commander and 63-member staff of the U.S. 7th
Fleet Task Force based in Subic Bay in the Philippines will be moved
to Yokosuka, Japan, this summer, the U.S. Navy said Friday.
   The Commander Task Force 70 is responsible for the USS Midway,
carrier Wing Five, and ships operating the Midway Battle Group, the
Navy said.
   The move will improve the fleet's operational readiness and save
money and time for ship and personnel movement between Subic Bay and
Yokosuka, the headquarters of the U.S. 7th Fleet, the Navy said.
Yokosuka is about 30 miles southwest of Tokyo.
