<SECOND>PM-Obit-Gallagher,0120</SECOND>
<HEAD>Communications Industry Newsletter Editor Dies at 79</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bernard P. Gallagher, founder and editor-in-chief
of the Gallagher Report, has died, two days after the communications
industry newsletter published its last issue. He was 79.
   Gallagher died Wednesday at New York Hospital, a week after he
had announced that he was retiring and folding the newsletter after
37 years. He cited his age and his inability to find a suitable
buyer.
   In addition to news about the communications industry, the
newsletter offered its readers speculation and such features as
listings of best and worst executives and advertisements.
   Gallagher is survived by his wife, Harriet, as well as a daughter
and a sister.
