<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--UnusualDiscipline     06-23 0161</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Unusual Discipline,0164</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Arrested For Putting Daughter On Leash, Making Her Bark Like
Dog</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man was arrested on child abuse and assault
charges after he allegedly tied a belt around his 13-year-old
daughter's neck and forced her to crawl down the street and bark
like a dog, police said.
   Joseph A. Dickson, 42, was released on $1,000 bail following
arraignment Thursday on charges of endangering the welfare of a
child and third-degree assault, said Albany Police Sgt. Robert
Wolfgang.
   Dickson is alleged to have forced the girl to crawl and bark
after she failed to return home on time Wednesday night, Wolfgang
said. ``Apparently he considered it a form of discipline for his
daughter,'' he said.
   ``I told her if you want to act like a dog, then you get down and
crawl like a dog,'' Dickson said at his arraignment.
   Police were called about 4 a.m. Thursday by neighbors who heard
the commotion.
