<FIRST>u f BC-Britain-Stocks 1stLd-Writethru   06-23 0163</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0170</SECOND>
<HEAD>Stock Prices Fall</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES with close</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices fell Friday after an erratic trading
session dominated by worries that British interest rates are headed
higher.
   The Financial Times Stock Index 100 index closed down 12.5
points, or 0.57 percent, at 2,167.5. Volume was a moderate 490.3
million shares, down from 498.2 million Thursday.
   An early surge on Wall Street lifted London shares well above
midday lows before the close.
   But dealers said the market was concerned the volatility of the
British pound would provoke another rise in base lending rates above
the current 14 percent.
   Traders said the market would likely remain nervous before
Tuesday's release of May trade data.
   Afternoon trading was disrupted by a computer failure at the
stock exchange that halted calculation of market indexes several
hours.
   Though the exchange's trading system wasn't affected, dealers
said many participants were reluctant to trade ``blind,'' without a
firm idea of minute-by-minute market trends.
</TEXT>
