<FIRST>r f BC-Universal-Europe     06-23 0194</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Universal-Europe,0203</SECOND>
<HEAD>MCA Planning Universal Studios Tour in Europe by 1993</HEAD>
<DATELINE>UNIVERSAL CITY, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   MCA Inc. plans to open a Universal
Studios tour in London or Paris by 1993, a year after the Euro
Disneyland theme park opens near Paris, company officials say.
   The theme park will include film studios and attractions
highlighting the Hollywood theme, and it will have hotels, specialty
shops, restaurants and perhaps a concert arena, Frank Stanek of MCA
Enterprises International told the Los Angeles Daily News in an
article published Friday.
   Europe is largely underdeveloped in American-type outdoor leisure
activities, he said. ``This is one thing Americans are still able to
export. There's a very high demand for theme parks worldwide.''
   Stanek said final site selection, expected by the end of the
year, depends on government incentives, land costs and availability.
   ``We have no concern about competing with Disney. Our products
are somewhat different,'' said Stanek.
   Disney also downplayed the rivalry with MCA.
   ``We don't look on MCA as competition,'' said Disney spokesman
Tom Deegan. ``We really don't think it's worth commenting on.
They've been talking about doing things _ Japan, Europe, Florida _
for years.''
</TEXT>
