<FIRST>r f AM-MemorexTelex     06-23 0171</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Memorex Telex,0177</SECOND>
<HEAD>Memorex Telex Co-President Joining Sooner Federal</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TULSA, Okla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   George Bragg, a co-president of Memorex Telex
Corp. in Tulsa, has resigned effective July 15 to become chairman
and chief executive officer of Sooner Federal Savings &amp; Loan
Association.
   Sooner also announced John Roberds, interim president, was
retained as president and chief operating officer of Sooner after
the board's previous acceptance of the resignation of W.R. Hagstrom,
former Sooner chairman and chief executive officer.
   Bragg had been with Telex Corp. eight years before its merger
with Memorex International NV in June 1988. He holds the office of
president of Memorex Telex jointly with Steve Jatras and Georgio
Ronchi.
   ``When we completed the merger, we agreed to stay with the
organization for one to two years to help in the transition, and we
agreed we would keep it open as to what would happen after that,''
Bragg said.
   ``The transition is complete. Memorex Telex is doing extremely
well, and I feel comfortable I can make a career change.''
</TEXT>
